rule: Caused by dissolution of cements or metastable framework grains (feldspars, rock fragments) in siliciclastic sedimentary rocks or dissolution of cements, fossils, framework crystals, etc. in carbonate or other chemically formed rocks
Arising from pore space in cements or among other authigenic minerals
Owing to fracturing of any type of rock by tectonic forces or other processes such as compaction and desiccation
Common removal of carbonate or sulphate minerals
